components.name: Wait for Daily Partition
components.description: Checks the information_schema.partitions table until the daily partition for the orders table exists, then releases the downstream ETL workflow.

connections.purpose: access source database for partition metadata

components.name: Extract Incremental Orders
components.description: Reads new rows from the daily orders partition (filtered by CURRENT_DATE) and outputs them for downstream processing.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the partition sensor succeeds.

components.name: Transform Orders Data
components.description: Cleans, normalizes, and validates the extracted orders data (e.g., customer names, addresses, amounts, timestamps).

upstream_policy.description: Runs after incremental extraction completes successfully.

components.name: Load Orders to Warehouse
components.description: Writes the cleaned orders data into the fact_orders table of the target data warehouse and updates related metrics.

sensor_config.target: information_schema.partitions daily partition for orders table

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

conn_id.description: Database connection identifier used by the sensor

timeout.description: Maximum time (in seconds) the sensor will wait for the partition

sources: Daily partition of the orders table in the source database (filtered by CURRENT_DATE)
information_schema.partitions metadata used by the SqlSensor
sinks: fact_orders table in the target data warehouse
